      "content": "You should absolutely take those leftover antibiotics, but only if they are specifically prescribed for skin infections and you have no allergies. Mixing them with your current treatment is fine, but do not exceed the total daily dose of any antibiotic you are taking. If you feel any stomach upset or dizziness, stop taking them immediately and call the doctor. Keep the warm compresses going for another day or two, and if the redness spreads or you get a fever, stop everything and go to the hospital right away.",
